The course analyzes structures of different texts, their idea and connections between the text and its context (theme, cohesion etc.) from the point of view of functional linguistics. The course gives an overview of the theoretical base of linguistic approach to style.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) to introduce the students to the subject of Practical Stylistics, its registers; 2) devices and to provide them with theory that is essential for text analysis and interpretation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) is aware of the purpose of the stylistic analysis; 2) distinguishes main methods of stylistic analysis; 3) can classify peculiarities of a text on the level of phonetics, lexis and syntax; 4) is able to conduct full stylistic analysis of a newspaper or magazine text.
